description: 1968: Two surfers in Santa Cruz, Calif., decide they're hungry... but they don't want to miss the next big wave. So they create a tasty, portable, hearty snack of mixed raisins and peanuts, inadvertantly conceiving the first trail mix. Soon thereafter, friends and family in Santa Cruz fell in love with the surfers' delicious, nutritious snacks and Harmony Foods was born. Through the years, Harmony developed hundreds of snack creations and marketed them to supermarket bulk food displays all over the country. Harmony was the first company to give its customers a taste of yogurt raisins, and they were one of the first to produce gummy bears.In 1978, Indiana-based Golden Stream Sprout Company, which grew alfalfa and bean sprouts and sold them in bulk to supermarkets, fell in love with Harmony snacks and later started to distribute them in the Midwest. Through the years, Golden Stream continued to grow and evolve, making its own nutritious snacks. Then in 2004, the two companies came full circle when Golden Stream purchased Harmony Foods. The combined company calls itself Harmony Foods, and the full line now includes trail mixes, dried fruits, nuts and seeds, sweet snacks, and organic snacks.Harmony Foods' Mission: To nourish healthy lifestyles by providing delicious, better-for-you snacks made with the highest quality, wholesome ingredients

description: The Stash Tea Company is headquartered in Tigard, Oregon, a suburb of Portland. Founded in 1972, Stash Tea originally operated out of an old Portland Victorian style house, supplying loose herbal teas and bulk herbs to natural food stores. Starting in 1975, the company broadened its focus to include bagged teas and then began to sell a full line of traditional, specialty blend and herbal teas directly to fine restaurants and through a mail-order catalog to consumers. Today, Stash Tea is enjoying steady growth and has become one of the largest specialty tea companies in the United States, with products available through foodservice, grocery stores, tea and coffee shops, club stores, mass merchandisers, natural foods stores, mail order, and the Internet. Stash Tea is also available in Canada and in several foreign countries.The company derives its name from an entertaining aspect of tea folklore. In earlier centuries, tea was a valuable commodity traditionally transported by clipper ship. The ship's captain often was presented with some of the finest teas for his personal use. This supply was his stash, stowed carefully as his private reserve. Today, the term still is used to denote anything put away carefully because of its preciousness

title: Jays Krunchers Kettle Cooked Potato Chips, Regular, 5-Ounce Bags (Pack of 20
description: Jays Foods has been making snacks at its South Side Chicago location since 1955In 1927, Leonard Japp, Sr. and a friend bought a rickety truck for $50--$5 down and the rest in payments. They used it to pick up their first load of pretzels, for $22.50. By 1929, the pair had a fleet of delivery trucks on the road, shiny new frying vats, and fair reason to believe the best was yet to come. Then the stock market crashed.Japp proved resilient, however, bouncing back by the mid-1930s with a new partner and a second go-round at snacks. The pair’s business flourished under their house brand, Mrs. Japp’s Potato Chips, until Pearl Harbor nearly drove them out of business because of the name’s negative connotation. We had to rename our company fast. The name Jays was available so we made it Jays Foods, Japp, Sr. says.With the potato chips back on the shelves under the Jays name, they became Chicago’s premier potato chip. Jays bolstered its position in the market by including recipes on its bags of chips created by Japp’s wife, Eugenia. With his successful business, Japp ventured into other snack territories and began manufacturing popcorn, pretzels, and tortilla chips. Jays Foods remained under family control until a decision to sell the company was made in 1986.At a 90th birthday party for Japp, Sr., the rumor was that Jays was on the selling block. Leonard Japp, Jr. turned to his father and asked Do you want to go back to work? To which the elder replied Yeah, why not. So the Japp family reacquired the company in 1994. Jays Foods was born again with the same commitment for quality snacks that has made them the Midwest’s premier snack manufacturer.Today, Jays manufactures and distributes a full line of quality snacks including its signature Jays Potato Chips, O-KE-DOKE popcorns, Krunchers! Potato Chips, and a line of Hot Stuff snacks. The company has been located in its 99th Street facility on the South Side of Chicago since 1955. If you're passing by, look for the semi-trucks full of potatoes being loaded onto Jays production line.

Jays Foods was born again with the same commitment for quality snacks that has made them the Midwest’s premier snack manufacturer.Today, Jays manufactures and distributes a full line of quality snacks including its signature Jays Potato Chips, O-KE-DOKE popcorns, Krunchers! Potato Chips, and a line of Hot Stuff snacks. The company has been located in its 99th Street facility on the South Side of Chicago since 1955. If you're passing by, look for the semi-trucks full of potatoes being loaded onto Jays production line.

title: Jays Potato Chips, Regular, 11.5-Ounce Bags (Pack of 10
description: Jays Foods has been making snacks at its South Side Chicago location since 1955In 1927, Leonard Japp, Sr. and a friend bought a rickety truck for $50--$5 down and the rest in payments. They used it to pick up their first load of pretzels, for $22.50. By 1929, the pair had a fleet of delivery trucks on the road, shiny new frying vats, and fair reason to believe the best was yet to come. Then the stock market crashed.Japp proved resilient, however, bouncing back by the mid-1930s with a new partner and a second go-round at snacks. The pair’s business flourished under their house brand, Mrs. Japp’s Potato Chips, until Pearl Harbor nearly drove them out of business because of the name’s negative connotation. We had to rename our company fast. The name Jays was available so we made it Jays Foods, Japp, Sr. says.With the potato chips back on the shelves under the Jays name, they became Chicago’s premier potato chip. Jays bolstered its position in the market by including recipes on its bags of chips created by Japp’s wife, Eugenia. With his successful business, Japp ventured into other snack territories and began manufacturing popcorn, pretzels, and tortilla chips. title: Sunridge Farms Organic Banana Chips, 5.5-Ounce Bags (Pack of 12)
description: SunRidge Farms is a true innovator in organic and natural bulk and packaged trail mixes, dried fruits, confections, and snack blends. Their commitment to natural ingredient development brings an array of flavors without the use of unhealthy refined sugars, hydrogenated oils, artificial colorings, or preservatives. SunRidge Farms offers a wide variety within each of their categories to suit almost every taste. SunRidge Farms is one of the most widely recognized and trusted names in bulk foods. Their goal is to continue to innovate while others follow, and in so doing, bring more and more healthy alternatives to the table. SunRidge Farms also feels that it is essential to contribute to the preservation of ecological diversity, wildlife, and natural terrain. Their donations support the successful resolution of environmental, social, food related, and world hunger issues.SunRidge Farms products include dried fruits, granolas and cereals, natural and organic candies, trail mixes, pastas, beans, and other grain blends, and a selection of delicious nuts and seed mixes. Family owned and operated since 1977, SunRidge Farms is based in Pajaro, California

title: Bob's Red Mill Banana Chips, 10-Ounce Packages (Pack of 4
description: Bob Moore's secret to life may just be work hard and keep it simple. Living this philosophy, Bob literally puts his nose to the grindstone every day. Bob's Red Mill Natural Foods is an Oregon-based company that utilizes simple, old-world technology to mill hundreds of all-natural whole grain products.Bob's Red Mill is dedicated to the manufacturing of natural foods in the natural way. In their own words: With all the sophisticated knowledge of recent times, no machinery has yet been developed that grinds grains into flour quite as well as our flint-hard quartz millstones quarried in France and used by discriminating millers since early Roman times.Our well-dressed (sharpened) sets of millstones turn the highest quality wheat into a finer, better baking bread flour than all the hammer mills, steel roller mills, steel buhr mills, or pulverizers ever built! These slow turning millstones grind the bran, endosperm, and germ (containing its nutritious wheat germ oil) into flour in a cool natural way, creating a more assimilable food.Bob's Red Mill stone grinds all common and most uncommon grains into flours and meals on its over 100-year-old mills. They mix them into an astounding array of unique cereals, pancake and waffle mixes, machine and hand-made bread mixes, quick bread mixes, gluten-free mixes, and specialty grain products.

title: PotatoFinger Potato Chips, Lightly Salted, 8-Ounce Bags (Pack of 12
description: Meet the King and Queen of Crunch: Owners Leon and Lainie Stoltz, self-professed potato chip aficionados, proudly distribute PotatoFinger Potato Chips to better grocery stores throughout the eastern United States. A like-minded pair of creative thinkers, they established PotatoFinger in 1999 as an incubator for special products and services that they have brought to market over the years. Their ultimate goal was to launch their own special line of potato chips under the PotatoFinger brand. The debut of PotatoFinger Potato Chips is the happy result of their quest for a chip with the perfect combination of crispness and flavor.PotatoFinger is based in Decatur, Georgia.PotatoFinger: How It All BeganPotatoFinger is a favorite nickname from owner Leon Stoltz's childhood years in South Africa. A potato chip snacker from an early age, his mom called him potato fingers because of the perpetual layer of potato chip residue left behind on his fingers and hands. As a grown-up, he trademarked his nickname, and began the long search for his very own potato chip recipe to manufacture.Introducing... Chipponie!ChipponieWhen PotatoFinger did a search for the right celebrity endorsement of their new potato chip line, they quickly found professional spokesmodel Chipponie and signed her, immediately and indefinitely, to be the face of PotatoFinger. Although Chipponie is in high demand for guest slots on several celebrity reality shows, her enthusiasm for PotatoFinger has taken precedence over all of her other projects. She now appears exclusively in promotional work for PotatoFinger. In a recent interview on a well-known late night cable news talk show Chipponie discussed this business relationship at length and summed it up saying I am sassy. I have attitude. PotatoFinger is an old-school company, distributing chips with attitude! We are a perfect match!PotatoFinger's Mission and ValuesIt is the mission of PotatoFinger to offer an exceptional potato chip to every customer. We use the highest quality potatoes and produce our chips to meet strict US food production standards. We value diversity, enthusiasm, integrity and teamwork. We respect our customers and each other. And we love potato chips.

title: PotatoFinger Potato Chips, Salt & Vinegar, 8-Ounce Bags (Pack of 12)
description: PotatoFinger Potato Chips are more than just delicious. They have attitude! They're sassy, fresh and appealing, just like the people who enjoy them. Cooked old school--thin and crispy, but with no hydrogenated oils or trans fats--PotatoFinger Potato Chips are a new twist on the classic chip, and a healthier alternative to other snacks.It All Starts with the Perfect PotatoPotatoFinger potato chips are made from natural, authentic chipper potatoes. Chipper potatoes are smaller and rounder than baking potatoes, and with less starch and lower sugar. They require a warm, moist climate to yield the highest quality. (A high starch potato turns brown when baked.) During the regular growing season, we use Atlantis potatoes freshly harvested from fields in the eastern US, starting in Florida, ending in late fall with harvests from Ohio. During the winter months we use Snowder potatoes from a greenhouse in Michigan. The potatoes are grown according to US EPA, USDA, and FDA standards. Neither variety is genetically altered.These Chips Win AwardsIn September 2005, PotatoFinger Old School Thin & Crispy Potato Chips was awarded second place in the best snack category in the Best of Atlanta awards at The Atlanta Gourmet Market. Other accolades include Gold Medal Awards from the American Taste Institute of San Francisco and Superior Product Awards from Food Distribution magazine.

title: Garden of Eatin' Tortilla Chips, Guacamole, 8.1 Ounce (Pack of 12
description: Garden of Eatin' was founded almost 35 years ago by Al Jacobson, a visionary who was always several steps ahead of his contemporaries. He first toyed with the idea of becoming a vegetarian in the early 1900s when as a toddler living on a farm in Pennsylvania, he discovered the family ate his favorite playmate, the chicken! Fast-forward to the 1940s when he dabbled in yoga and metaphysics and became a traveling product demonstrator for Hain Pure Foods, an organic company on the West Coast.In the early 1970s, Al let his spiritual side guide him to start his own health food company--Garden of Eatin’ with the launch of Bible Bread, organic whole wheat pita. Then in 1986, after he followed his natural health instincts and purchased tons of organic blue corn, Al decided to produce Blue Corn Chips. In keeping with his unorthodox approach, the chips were launched at a major fancy foods show and they took off! Since then, Garden of Eatin’ has introduced more than 20 varieties of all-natural tortilla chips, each of them true to Al’s inspiring outlook on life and healthy snacks.In 1998, Garden of Eatin’ became a part of The Hain Celestial Group, Inc., a natural and organic foods company Dedicated to a Healthy Way of Life. Since then, Garden of Eatin’ has expanded its product line into several new categories including: Organic Taco Shells and Taco Dinner Kits; Organic Microwave Popcorn; Pita Chips; and Toasted Corn Nuts.The Garden of Eatin' family of products contains no trans fat or hydrogenated oils, are all natural and Kosher certified. So no matter who enjoys these distinctive snacks, you’ll serve them with pride knowing they’re from a trusted brand

title: Garden of Eatin' Pita Chips, Sea Salt, 6 Ounce (Pack of 12
description: Garden of Eatin' was founded almost 35 years ago by Al Jacobson, a visionary who was always several steps ahead of his contemporaries. He first toyed with the idea of becoming a vegetarian in the early 1900s when as a toddler living on a farm in Pennsylvania, he discovered the family ate his favorite playmate, the chicken! Fast-forward to the 1940s when he dabbled in yoga and metaphysics and became a traveling product demonstrator for Hain Pure Foods, an organic company on the West Coast.In the early 1970s, Al let his spiritual side guide him to start his own health food company--Garden of Eatin’ with the launch of Bible Bread, organic whole wheat pita. Then in 1986, after he followed his natural health instincts and purchased tons of organic blue corn, Al decided to produce Blue Corn Chips. In keeping with his unorthodox approach, the chips were launched at a major fancy foods show and they took off! Since then, Garden of Eatin’ has introduced more than 20 varieties of all-natural tortilla chips, each of them true to Al’s inspiring outlook on life and healthy snacks.In 1998, Garden of Eatin’ became a part of The Hain Celestial Group, Inc., a natural and organic foods company Dedicated to a Healthy Way of Life. Since then, Garden of Eatin’ has expanded its product line into several new categories including: Organic Taco Shells and Taco Dinner Kits; Organic Microwave Popcorn; Pita Chips; and Toasted Corn Nuts.The Garden of Eatin' family of products contains no trans fat or hydrogenated oils, are all natural and Kosher certified. So no matter who enjoys these distinctive snacks, you’ll serve them with pride knowing they’re from a trusted brand.

title: Melissa's Dried Coconut Chips, 3-Ounce Bags (Pack of 12
description: The World Variety Produce Inc. warehouse in Los Angeles.Established in 1984 and located in the Vernon district of Los Angeles, California, Melissa's/World Variety Produce began strictly as a source of specialty produce. Joe Hernandez, a Texas native, founded the business with a decade of produce industry experience in a small, rented produce warehouse lunchroom. The original office had one telephone and two chairs--no one could have guessed that, within a few short years, the company would occupy a newly renovated and expanded 280,000 square foot office, warehouse complex, and state-of-the-art CCOF/QAI Certified Organic Packing Facility.World Variety Produce markets product under specially-developed brand names: Melissa's, Don Enrique, Rookies, and Jo-San brand. Consumers everywhere recognize the Melissa's logo, in cheerful red with a carrot standing in for the letter I. In 1986, seeking a more inviting label than possible with the World Variety corporate identity, Hernandez named this well-known brand after his daughter. Melissa Hernandez has recently taken an active role in the business. Periodically, she appears at the industry conventions and press events as a company spokesperson--and yes, even in her early 20s, she knows the product line very well.Family is a big part of World Variety’s success. Through the years, the company has found stable growth thanks to the support of very loyal customers and a close-knit family of employees dedicated to customer service. After all, Hernandez has made the company philosophy straightforward: Give the customers what they want and keep them happy.World Variety is committed to industry and consumer education about specialty produce. Product headers include recipes, serving suggestions, and nutritional information. Melissa's/World Variety Produce will continue with its product innovations and customer-satisfying service. You can never slack off, says Hernandez. ...the little guys will catch up if you get over-confident. You can count on World Variety for the Freshest Ideas in Produce. The tag line--more than good advertising--is a company promise to provide product and service beyond expectation.

title: Pringles Potato Crisps, Jalapeno, 5.75-Ounce Packages (Pack of 14
description: Pringles, which first launched in October 1968, makes its unique snacks using dried potatoes that are cooked and mashed with just enough water and other wholesome ingredients added to form a smooth potato dough. Then, the dough is cut and placed on Pringle-shaped carriers (for that one-of-a-kind shape), fried, and seasoned just right on one side. Then, using special equipment, they're stacked into the unique Pringles cans.The Pringles name came about in the late 1960s, when the company made a list of street names from a Cincinnati phone book that began with P. Pringle Avenue in Finneytown was available for trademark, and its sound appealed to the brand.The first Pringles were packaged in a tall, cylindrical metal can with a red wrapper. The brand expanded nationally in May 1975. Many different flavors and varieties came and went in the 1970s and 1980s, but the most significant breakthrough occurred in September 1996 with the launch of Fat Free Pringles, with P&G;'s olestra fat substitute.Pringles is a member of the Proctor & Gamble family of brands.About Proctor & GambleTwo billion times a day, Proctor & Gamble brands touch the lives of people around the world. The company has one of the largest and strongest portfolios of trusted brands in the world, including Pampers, Tide, Ariel, Always, Pantene, Bounty, Folgers, Pringles, Charmin, Downy, Iams, Crest, Actonel, and Olay.It all started in 1837 when William Procter and James Gamble settled in Cincinnati. Procter quickly established himself as a candle maker, while Gamble apprenticed himself to a soap maker. The two might never have met had they not married sisters, Olivia and Elizabeth Norris, whose father convinced his new sons-in-law to become business partners. In 1837,a bold new enterprise was born: Procter & Gamble. By each pledging $3,596.47 to the new venture, they began selling soap and candles. Twenty-two years later, their business exceeded $1 million in sales. By 1980 that figure would reach $10 billion, and by 1993 the company would generate over $35 billion in revenue.

title: A & J's Lasagna Chips, The Wild West Barbecue Flavor, 5-Ounce Bags (Pack of 12
description: When A&J;'s Lasagna Chips' founder, nutritionist and nurse Elaine Katz, received a call from school nurses that her 5-year-old Jared was hyperactive, it was cause for great distress. At the time, some 30 years ago, the term ADD wasn’t loosely thrown around as a common explanation for children’s excited behavior. It was a big stigma then, Elaine said. Elaine explored natural diets as a means to help her son. Not wanting to take the easy way out through medicine, she sought the help of Dr. Feingold, inventor of the Feingold Diet, which calls for no artificial preservatives or additives in food products. She soon discovered that preservatives such as BHA and BHT found in most snacks would cause her son to bounce off the wall.All-natural supermarkets were non-existent at the time, so finding all-natural snacks was a challenge. This prompted Elaine to create her own snack--a chip made from fresh sheets of lasagna. Using unbleached semolina flour, specially seasoned and cooked, she produced the only all-natural pasta chip with no artificial ingredients, no cholesterol, and 50% less fat than other leading snack chips. Despite the healthy ingredients, this snack became a huge hit among Jared’s classmates, selling for 10 cents a chip at bake sales and becoming the most popular snack at friends’ parties. Parents loved this new snack, too.In the early '90s, while living on Long Island, Elaine tried turning her invention into a business. She began making samples out of her garage and received positive response from people tasting it. But, the demands of motherhood proved to be too great to juggle a business as well. It was her now-adult son Jared who recently turned his mother’s old venture into a reality.

description: John A. McDougall, M.D.--physician, nutrition expert, and founder of Dr. McDougall's Right Foods--has been studying, writing, and speaking out about the effects of nutrition on health for more than 20 years and is one of the founding fathers of modern wellness. Dr. McDougall believes that people should look and feel great, and should enjoy optimal health for a lifetime.Unfortunately, many people compromise their health unknowingly through poor dietary habits. Dr. McDougall should know. He suffered a stroke at the age of 18 then developed an interest in medicine. He went on not only to reverse his own health and enjoy life, but to teach thousands how to enjoy good health themselves.Dr. McDougall is founder and medical director of the nationally renowned McDougall Program in Santa Rosa, California. Based on several years of private practice with thousands of patients and extensive medical research, Dr. McDougall has developed a nourishing, low-fat diet that not only promotes a broad range of health benefits such as weight loss, but more importantly can reverse serious illness, such as heart disease, without drugs.A graduate of Michigan State University's College of Human Medicine, Dr. McDougall performed his internship at Queen's Medical Center in Honolulu, Hawaii, and his medical residency at the University of Hawaii. He is certified as an internist by the Board of Internal Medicine and the National Board of Medical Examiners. He has authored (or co-authored with his wife, Mary) ten best-selling books about the connection between nutrition and health, and is a frequent lecturer and talk show guest. He enjoys travel, wind surfing, and hiking. A few times a year, Dr. McDougall leads adventure and wellness trips to exotic locations serving McDougall style foods. Guests return feeling fit and healthy.All of Dr. McDougall's instant meal cups are all-natural, absolutely delicious, very low in fat, satisfying, nutritious, quick and easy to prepare, developed by a medical doctor, free of cholesteral, vegetarian, and non-dairy.

Dr. McDougall believes that people should look and feel great, and should enjoy optimal health for a lifetime.Unfortunately, many people compromise their health unknowingly through poor dietary habits. Dr. McDougall should know. He suffered a stroke at the age of 18 then developed an interest in medicine. He went on not only to reverse his own health and enjoy life, but to teach thousands how to enjoy good health themselves.Dr. McDougall is founder and medical director of the nationally renowned McDougall Program in Santa Rosa, California. Based on several years of private practice with thousands of patients and extensive medical research, Dr. McDougall has developed a nourishing, low-fat diet that not only promotes a broad range of health benefits such as weight loss, but more importantly can reverse serious illness, such as heart disease, without drugs.A graduate of Michigan State University's College of Human Medicine, Dr. McDougall performed his internship at Queen's Medical Center in Honolulu, Hawaii, and his medical residency at the University of Hawaii. He is certified as an internist by the Board of Internal Medicine and the National Board of Medical Examiners. He has authored (or co-authored with his wife, Mary) ten best-selling books about the connection between nutrition and health, and is a frequent lecturer and talk show guest. He enjoys travel, wind surfing, and hiking. A few times a year, Dr. McDougall leads adventure and wellness trips to exotic locations serving McDougall style foods. Guests return feeling fit and healthy.All of Dr. McDougall's instant meal cups are all-natural, absolutely delicious, very low in fat, satisfying, nutritious, quick and easy to prepare, developed by a medical doctor, free of cholesteral, vegetarian, and non-dairy

description: In 1906, Paul A. Mariani, Sr., an immigrant from the Mediterranean region known for growing fruit, arrived in California and started Mariani Packing Co., Inc. The beginnings were humble with the family growing most of its own fruit and packing it into wooden boxes for export markets.In the early 1940s, his son, Paul A. Mariani, Jr., developed, for the first time, a moist dried fruit product that did not have to be rehydrated at home. Through this innovation, the business grew and perfected working partnerships with major supermarkets throughout the country.In 1979, Paul Mariani Sr.'s grandson, Mark A. Mariani, became responsible for its legacy. From the company's solid foundation, he has grown the business and the company now sells more than 125 million pounds of product annually. It is a dominant brand for quality dried fruit in the retail sector of supermarkets and is also known for the premium ingredients it sells to Fortune 500 companies. 2006 marks the 100th anniversary of Paul Mariani’s humble beginnings. Today, four generations later, the Mariani Packing Company is still family owned and operated and has grown to become the largest independent dried fruit producer in the world.The company has its home office in Vacaville, Calif., with four other processing sites throughout California, the largest having 18 acres under roof. The family continues to follow the vision set by Paul A. Mariani, Sr. with Mark A. Mariani as Chairman/CEO and great grandson, George Sousa, Jr., as President. They are committed to the early lessons of their predecessors:Mutual RespectEmbrace ChangeContinuous ImprovementNever Compromise on QualityBuild for the Futur

title: Madhouse Munchies Sea Salt & Vinegar Potato Chips, 5-Ounce Bags (Pack of 12)
description: In 1996 I left the financial markets and set out for the clear skies and wide-open spaces of Vermont to pursue my vision of the perfect potato chip. Four years later, I have never looked back and have never eaten better! I first started by hand-slicing small batches of fresh New England potatoes into a small French-fry cooker I borrowed from a friend with a restaurant. I experimented for months testing different oils, potatoes and seasoned toppings. My plan was simple; not to give up until I had discovered the point at which perfect flavor merged with a healthy, simple recipe. Eventually, I found that perfect recipe: Select North American potatoes cooked in pure high-monounsaturated canola oil and topped with only all natural spices, herbs and sea salt. Nothing artificial is used, ever - only simple, premium, healthful and naturally delicious ingredients go into making our chips. Life became a Madhouse from that point on! As word got out about our recipes, our popularity among chip connoisseurs grew at a frantic pace. While we have been copied and shoved-around by the Big Guys in the chip world, they just can't seem to get it right, and for now, our unique micro-chips are, alone, at the top. I certainly hope that you enjoy Madhouse Munchies as much as we do. Enjoy! Jim Ehlen, Founder

title: Stacy's Pita Chips, Tuscan Herb, 6-Ounce Bags (Pack of 12
description: Everyone asks, How did a social worker and a psychologist, fresh out of graduate school, get into the snack food business? The social worker, Stacy Madison and the psychologist, Mark Andrus shared a passion for good food and a commitment to staying healthy. Here's their story: We decided to open a downtown Boston restaurant. However, large student loans and no capital halted our dream. So we decided to take a risk. We designed a food cart and began serving healthy pita bread roll-up sandwiches. They were an instant hit and the lines grew longer each day. As an incentive for customers to wait in line, we baked fresh pita bread into different flavored chips. Customers loved them so much, they encouraged us to get the chips into stores. We listened, and that's how Stacy's Pita Chip Company was born. Thanks to our loyal customers, our chips are now available nationwide.

description: In 1976, the founder and president of Seasons’ Enterprises, Ltd., Michael Season, moved his wife and children from Illinois to Oregon to try his hand at organic farming. Michael realized that there was a market for healthy, additive-free foods. In 1993, he introduced what is now one of the company’s most successful products—Michael Season’s Thin & Crispy Potato Chips. These great-tasting, reduced fat chips are also popular with a growing number of consumers with allergies or dietary limitations. title: Tropic Max Spicy Plantain Chips - 3 oz
description: Grown in the tropical areas of Ecuador, South America, Tropic Max selected plantains are carefully harvested by hand, sliced and delicately golden-crisped to create a delicious, nutritious tropical fruit chip, Rich in Potassium, Fiber, Vitamin A and Vitamin C, no cholesterol, artificial colors, flavors, or added preservatives.Try them as a naturally healthy great tasting tropical snack.What is a Plantain ?Plantains are similar to bananas. In fact, they are considered the cousin of the banana. However, Anyone who has ever accidentally eaten plantains instead of bananas will most likely not have a problem telling the two fruits apart. If bananas are the dessert, then plantains would be the mashed potatoes. Plantains look very similar to their sweeter banana cousins, but they are much starchier in consistency and blander in taste. Plantains grow in the same tropical regions as bananas, but they are not used for the same culinary purposes.Some sources suggest that plantains should never be eaten raw or in their unripened green stage. Others say that plantains can be eaten throughout their entire ripening period, but must be prepared properly for their changing taste and texture. Plantains in their earliest stages have a green skin which cannot be peeled off easily. Cooks using plantains at this stage often cut them into two inch (5 cm) sections and boil them until they are the consistency of boiled potatoes.As plantains continue to ripen, they become more of a yellow-orange than their bright yellow banana counterparts. They are still not sweet, but their flavor is not as bland as during the green stage. Finally, plantains ripen to a dark black color just before spoiling. Plantains at the overripe stage are almost as sweet as bananas, and can be peeled by hand. Shoppers looking for a different kind of banana for cooking should consider buying these black-skinned plantains.

title: CrispRoot Cassava Chips, Thai Ginger, 5-Ounce Bags (Pack of 12)
description: With their own humble beginnings, founders Hermanto Hidajat and Angela Ichwan founded Arico Natural Foods in 2004 with a big dream – to make a positive difference in the world. The inspiration came from Angela’s niece, Ella, who is Autistic & lives gluten- and dairy-free. Their travels also revealed to them that there are very few products out there for food-allergy sufferers that don’t also compromise taste and nutrition. After working at Fortune 100 companies and for leaders in the global food industry, Angela and Hermanto decided to leverage their backgrounds in food science and engineering – and their mutual passion for bettering the world - and start their own natural foods company. They sought to create delicious products without sacrificing the nutritional benefits they wanted to provide their customers. They began by developing a product line of four snack bars that not only delight the senses, but are also high in fiber, protein, calcium and contain only all-natural ingredients. Since the original launch of cookie bars, Arico has brought to market a line of cookie pouches and cassava chips. Arico’s all-natural snacks embrace Mindful Snacking to the fullest, containing only the highest-quality, most flavorful and most nutritious ingredients. Not only does Arico create a safe alternative for allergy sufferers, it strives to set an example for the rest of the world through a caring and sensitive business approach to its retail partners and consumers.Arico Natural Foods is committed to being a socially & environmentally conscious company. They purchase carbon offsets from Bonneville Environmental Foundation to offset the carbon emissions produced by its business operations. In 2007, Arico became the world’s first carbon-neutral gluten-free snack company. Arico’s annual purchase of carbon offsets through BEF is equivalent to planting approximately 28 acres of trees, or not driving a car for almost 20 years or 250,762 miles. Arico also partners with American Forests to plant a tree for every new store that carries its Cassava Chips. In 2007, Arico planted trees on the Indonesian island of Sumatra to help preserve the habitat of the endangered orangutan. In 2008, Arico supported a tree-planting project in Oregon’s Deschutes National Forest to restore wild forest fire destruction. Most important to Arico Natural Foods is supporting Women for Women International, a nonprofit organization providing women survivors of war with the skills to rebuild their lives and cause change in their communities. For more information, visit www.womenforwomen.org

title: Healthwise Low Acid Columbian Gourmet Supremo Decaffeinated Coffee, 12 Ounce
description: HealthWise Gourmet Coffees use Colombian Arabica Supremo beans exclusively, one of the highest grades of coffee beans available. The company roasts coffee in small batches to ensure quality and consistency. The TechnoRoasting process eliminates acids and irritants, which helps all who suffer from heartburn or stomach conditions exacerbated by acid. Instead of compromising flavor, the process also reduces bitterness and harshness common to other coffee products, which leaves a rich and mellow taste. The same process also protects the original minerals and micro-nutrients from coffee beans that many health-care products leverage. This contrasts with the roasting processes most often used by others, which typically destroys the compounds within coffee beans that offer many health benefits. An additional benefit of this process allows a pot to remain on a burner for hours without becoming increasingly bitter, a common consequence of other roasting methods. Similarly, you can refrigerate HealthWise coffee for up to one week, reheat it to below boiling, and the tast will remain unchanged from the original brewed cup. The total yield from a 12-ounce can, 110 cups, exceeds other brands as well since you do not have to use as many beans to make a full-flavored cup or pot.

title: Good Health Inc. Kettle Style Olive Oil Potato Chips Sea Salt -- 5 oz
description: For centuries, olive oil has been one of the mainstays of the Mediterranean diet. While the ancients may not have fully understood the nutritional value of the oil, they definitely appreciated its flavor. Today, olive oil evokes images of the old country with it simpler and slightly slower lifestyle - what we like to think of as the good life. We think that it would be great if everyone could move to the Mediterranean for awhile to experience this directly, but for now we will content ourselves with bringing a small bit of the region to you through this bag of wonderfully flavored kettle style Olive Oil Potato Chips. Oh, and did we mention that olive oil is healthy too? Rich in anti-oxidants and unsaturated fat, olive oil contains both omega-3 and omega-6 fatty acids which are important parts of a heart-healthy diet. Perhaps it is their consumption of olive oil that is partially responsible for the lower rates of stroke, heart disease among Greeks. In our Olive Oil Potato Chips, we at Good Health Natural Foods capture both the health benefits and flavor of one of mankind's greatest culinary achievements.

title: Michael Season's Kettle Cooked Jalapeno Potato Chips, 2 Ounce Bags (Pack of 24
description: In 1976, the founder and president of Seasons’ Enterprises, Ltd., Michael Season, moved his wife and children from Illinois to Oregon to try his hand at organic farming. From that Oregon farm, the family developed one of the largest natural foods distributorships in the U.S. When the family returned to the Midwest, Michael started what is known today as Michael Season’s brand potato chips, and the product quickly gained a loyal following. Michael realized that there was a market for healthy, additive-free foods. In 1993, he introduced what is now one of the company’s most successful products—Michael Season’s Thin & Crispy Potato Chips. These great-tasting, reduced fat chips are also popular with a growing number of consumers with allergies or dietary limitations. Michael Season’s is committed to using all-natural ingredients and providing an exceptional product at an affordable price.

That just puts a lot of stuff in there that they could all do without. They never bake their chips either. That just takes a lot of flavor out, which, as snackers, they simply can't do without. So they came up with a chip like no snack aisle has seen (or taste bud has tasted). Thanks to the magic of popping, they found a way to pop all the flavor in, while keeping fake stuff and at least half the fat of regular flavored chips out. The Magic of PoppingPopping is a way of making their naturally delicious chips. They start with the finest ingredients, add a little heat and pressure, and pop! It's a chip. All that's added is a flavorful blend of seasonings to create taste-bud popping flavors that appeal to the whole family. Pop open a bag of popchips and try for yourself. Everybody has a favorite. description: Yes its finally here! The amazing Cacao Butter melts, not just any cocoa butter but Premium Grade-A Raw Edible Cacao! It took us a long time to find the best Cacao farms, and they had to be fair-trade plus Certified Organic and offer us only the freshest batches, but we did it! We are proud to offer such amazing quality of premium Cacao to our beloved customers like never before. This has been a highly requested item and had been on our 'to do' list for a while so here you go, indulge & enjoy! Our amazing little Cocoa Butter Melts come in small disc shaped chips that are easy to use right away and melt at body temperature. You should try baking with it, brownies, cakes etc and enjoy the natural chocolate aroma filling your kitchen. Throw a few melts into your warm bath water and dive in for a luxurious skin nourishing and mind revitalizing bath. This might get addictive! Just try our Cocoa (Cacao) Butter once and you will be hooked. You will truly be enticed by the rich deep aroma of our Cacao Butter, smooth texture and full bodied flavor. Smell how fresh it is as soon as you open the pack! Do your skin a favor just try GreenPlanet-Organic's Organic Cocoa Butter Melts once, you're sure to come back for more! **Test our True Cocoa (Cacao) Butter: Leave an open container of our Cocoa Butter in a closed room and leave the room for some time. When you open the door and walk back in you will be taken by the wonderful delicious aroma and your room is now filled with the smooth, rich chocolate scent. True Cacao Butter is hard since it is NOT mixed with a base butter to dilute it. It easily melts once temperature is raised. ****This True Cacao Butter is shipped & sold by GreenPlanet-Organics and should arrive only with our packaging and logo to ensure genuine product**If you receive this from vendors other than us, do not use and demand a full refund immediately**

title: Jackson's Honest Organic Sweet Potato Chips Sea Salt -- 5 o
description: The goal at Jackson's Honest Potato Chips is to bring the potato chip back to its humble and simple roots by using the finest organic potatoes available and kettle frying them by hand using organic coconut oil. Why Coconut Oil?For starters it is nature's most unique cooking oil: highly stable, full of good medium chain tryglycerides, and nature's most potent source of lauric acid. In our family, we've used organic coconut oil as an essential part of a diet that helped stabilize our son Jackson's illness; it's become a staple in our own kitchen ever since and it's why these chips are named after our son, Jackson. But we also use it because it gives our chips the best flavor and crunch. Industrially processed polyunsaturated vegetable oils just don't cut it anymore: try a chip cooked the way they were meant to be, in coconut oil. It will change your potato chip expectations forever. Made exclusively with organic potatoes and organic coconut oil and naturally gluten-free. We hope you will enjoy Jackson's Honest Potato Chips as much as we enjoy making them. From our kitchen to yours: honest in every way.

Coconut oil has been used for thousands of years by cultures around the world for its many health benefits.Another advantage is flavor! If you're tired of bland potato chips fried in polyunsaturated vegetable oils, try Jackson's Honest Potato Chips today. They're unlike any chip you've ever tasted.
